<TITLE> We want to change Bangladesh: Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 9 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League president Sheikh Hasina has greeted Bangladeshis on Eid ul-Azha celebrations and urged them to vote with conscience. "I congratulate all on the occasion of Eid. I wish happiness and peace to every person of the country," the former prime minister said in her Eid greetings on Tuesday. She has called upon all to work together, inspired by the significance of the sacrifice of Eid ul-Azha. The AL chief exchanged Eid greetings at her Dhanmondi office with diplomats and people from broader spectrum of society from 9:30am. "I call upon people to pray for the betterment of the country. People will live in peace if we take the lesson of sacrifice from the festival," she told reporters. The AL chief asked all to cast ballots with their conscience. "We want to change Bangladesh. We want all people to celebrate Eid with festivity." "I love my countrymen. I am ready to make any kind of sacrifice for the sake of the people," she said. Hasina also exchanged greetings with the so-called reformist leaders of the party and took photographs with them. bd
